content:
Create Permission Sets for Case Feed

After enabling Case Feed, create a permission set to give users access to it.

Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.
User Permissions:
Manage Profiles and Permission Sets.

To create permission sets:

1. On the Permission Set page, click App Permissions.
2. Select Use Case Feed. Optionally, select any other permissions you want to include in the set.
3. Click Save.

TIP: If editing an existing permission set, enabling Use Case Feed affects field visibility on Printable View pages.

See Also:
Set Up Cases for Salesforce Classic
Assign Case Feed to Users
title: Service Cloud Permission Sets
